<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Iran-AirFrance     09-07 0107</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Iran-Air France,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>French Carrier To Resume Service To Tehran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air France, the French national carrier, says it
will resume flights between Paris and Tehran next month after a
break of more than three years.
   Air France stopped its service to Tehran in March 1985 after
deciding the safety of its flights could not be assured, given the
political-military situation of the Iran-Iraq war.
   The airline announced Tuesday that it will schedule one flight a
week to Iran's capital, an Airbus A300 with first, business and
economy classes.
   Prior to March 1985, Air France offered two flights a week
between Paris and Tehran.
</TEXT>
