<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Sonny the Elephant,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sonny's Back After Labor Day Excursion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLOVIS, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sonny the elephant was coaxed home with a
trail of food after he climbed out of his pen, ripped out an
electrical wire designed to keep him enclosed and walked through a
chain-link fence.
   ``Most people think that elephants can't climb, but he can,''
city parks and recreation director Ash Grandy said Tuesday.
   The elephant was found Monday wandering in a vacant enclosure
next to his pen at Hillcrest Park Zoo.
   Using the lure of food ``was sort of like leading a donkey with
a carrot tied to the end of a stick,'' Grandy said.
   Sonny has been awaiting shipment to a new home at the Popcorn
Park Zoo near Newark, N.J., where he will be surrounded by a moat.
Zoo officials here decided to get rid of him because he has become
too large.
</TEXT>
