<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Lites SUB a0450 09-07 0220</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Lites, SUB, a0450,0225</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS final graf of 2nd item to restore first reference to
White</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lisa Pupo has promised to retaliate against
her law partners for pulling a prank that got her hundreds of
offers for a date, but admits it's tough to top a stunt that got
the attention of 56,800 people.
   At Sunday's National Football League game between the Dallas
Cowboys and the Pittsburgh Steelers, an airplane flew over the
stadium pulling a banner that read, ``LISA PUPO _ 30 _ SINGLE,''
along wither her home phone number.
   ``I must have gotten 200 phone calls. I got calls even before
the game was over,'' Miss Pupo said.
   ``I got marriage proposals, a couple of perverted calls, a lot
of pretty sincere callers and even a woman who wanted to know why I
would do such a thing,'' she said.
   ``I highly recommend it for someone who really is looking for a
date,'' she said., adding she was having her phone number changed.
   Miss Pupo said partners Mike Burns offered her the law firm's
tickets to the season opener. So she invited her parents, a friend
_ and her boyfriend _ to the game.
   She said she has warned Burns and David White to ``watch their
backs. I told them revenge is sweet.''
</TEXT>
