<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--RoyRogers-Arrest     09-07 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Roy Rogers-Arrest,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Named Roy Rogers To The Rescue in Bank Heist</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roy Rogers chased, tackled and captured a
bank robbery suspect, authorities said, but the hero in the
real-life drama isn't married to Dale Evans and never rode a horse
called Trigger.
   ``I just saw the guy and did what I thought ought to be done,''
Rogers, 38, of Tulsa said after Tuesday's action.
   Rogers captured Rodney McDonald, 45, of Bartlesville, a block
from a Fourth Century National Bank branch moments after the
holdup, said FBI spokesman Dan Vogel.
   Vogel said bank robbery charges will be sought against McDonald.
   Authorities said Rogers began chasing McDonald after seeing a
bank employee chasing the man. Rogers and the unidentified employee
restrained the unarmed suspect until police arrived.
   The bank was robbed by a man with a rectangular object he
claimed was bomb, but turned out not to be an explosive, police
said.
</TEXT>
