<HEAD>Cosby, Steinem Among NYC Power Brokers</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf to fix word order; Manhattan, inc. is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Big Apple's movers and shakers range from
such elected officials as Mayor Edward I. Koch and Gov. Mario Cuomo
to former President Richard Nixon and entertainer Bill Cosby, says
Manhattan, inc. magazine.
   Many hands ``grip the decision-making process,'' the magazine's
September issue said in listing New York's top power brokers.
   The list also includes investment banker Felix Rohatyn,
consultant Henry Kissinger, the former secretary of state;
socialite-philanthropist Brooke Astor; American Express chairman
James Robinson III; and gossip columnist Liz Smith.
   Also, Harlem minister Calvin Butts; theatrical producer Joseph
Papp of the New York Shakespeare Festival; New York Times Publisher
Arthur Ochs Sulzberger; feminists Gloria Steinem and Betty Friedan;
philanthropist-banker David Rockefeller; developer Donald Trump;
author Norman Mailer; Roman Catholic Cardinal John O'Connor; and
New Yorker magazine writer and preservationist Brendan Gill; and
Laurence Tisch, chairman of Loews Corp., CBS and New York
University.
