<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Britain-IceCream     09-07 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Britain-Ice Cream,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ice Cream Stripes Too Bright For Old Market Square</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHIPPING CAMPDEN, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two ice-cream sellers have been
ordered to stay away from the market square in this town because
the color of their tricycles clashes with the buildings.
   Councilors say the vanila and strawberry stripes on Lindsey and
Joanne Rastell's tricycles don't match the soft yellow stone
structures built centuries ago in this village of 1,600.
   ``These trikes look like very bright Victorian hat boxes _ they
are just not Campden,'' said councilwoman Juliette Griffiths on
Tuesday. ``If we let them stay, we shall have a fish-and-chip van
next.''
   Joanne Lindsey said the vendors would fight the move. ``We have
got a trading license from Cotswold district council and we plan to
stay,'' she said.
</TEXT>
