<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Israel-Guerrillas     09-07 0116</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Israel-Guerrillas,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Israel Releases Four Palestinian Guerrillas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli officials freed four Palestinian
guerrillas who were jailed after being captured off the coast of
Lebanon last year and flew them to Switzerland, the army command
said today.
   The four were among 50 Palestine Liberation Organization
guerrillas taken prisoner in February 1987 after the navy captured
a boat, the Maria R, en route from Cyprus to Lebanon.
   An army spokeswoman said all the guerrillas have been sentenced
to varying terms in jail. She did not elaborate.
   The four guerrillas released have completed their prison terms,
she said, adding that they were taken to Switzerland Tuesday night
to allow them to return to Arab countries.
</TEXT>
