<1ST_LINE>r a PM-PostManagement     09-07 0218</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Post Management,0223</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Houston Post Owner Dean Singleton Is New Publisher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   William Dean Singleton, chief executive officer
of the company that owns The Houston Post, has become the
newspaper's publisher, the Post reported today.
   Singleton, MediaNews Group's vice chairman and chief executive
officer, became publisher of the Post on Tuesday.
   Donald F. Hunt, the former publisher, has been named president
of MediaNews International, a new company owned by Singleton and
MediaNews chairman Richard Scudder, which was formed for
international acquisitions.
   Singleton and Scudder own MediaNews Group, parent company of the
Post, The Denver Post and 47 other newspapers in nine states.
   ``We decided several months ago that we wanted to expand our
operations outside the United States,'' Singleton said. ``Our
newspapers have been very successful here, and there are some good
opportunities in Great Britian and other parts of the world. We
wanted someone with international experience to run the company and
Don has that experience.''
   Hunt held several positions with Canadian newspapers including a
stint as general manager of The Toronto Sun before he moved to
Houston.
   Singleton moved from Dallas to Houston after he announced in
June that MediaNews Group had sold The Dallas Times Herald. At the
same time, he announced that MediaNews Group was moving its
corporate headquarters to Houston.
</TEXT>
