<HEAD>Possible Successor To East German Leader Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Werner Felfe, the East German secretary of
agriculture who has been mentioned as a possible successor to
Communist leader Erich Honecker, died today, the state-run ADN news
agency said.
   Felfe, 60, was one of the youngest members of the East Germany's
22-member Politburo. The cause of his death was not given.
   Felfe had in recent months spoken in favor of Soviet leader
Mikhail S. Gorbachev's reform plans, and told Western visitors that
similar reforms were needed in East Germany.
   He was one of the names frequently mentioned in the news media
as a possible successor to the 76-year-old Honecker.
</TEXT>
