<HEAD>Post Office Says Mail Early for Christmas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In what may be the first sure sign of autumn,
the U.S. Postal Service is reminding Americans to mail early for
Christmas, especially packages for military men and women and
others living abroad.
   ``It's never too early to mail packages overseas or to the
military,'' the agency says in the current edition of Postal
Bulletin,'' a publication for postal workers and managers.
   The Bulletin suggested these mailing dates, to assure delivery
by Christmas:
   Oct. 3 _ Civilian surface mail to Africa, Australia and
Southeast Asia.
   Oct. 14 _ Civilian surface mail to the Far East and Middle East.
   Oct. 16 _ Military surface mail to Australia, Europe and the Far
East.
   Oct. 27 _ Military space available mail to Africa.
   Oct. 31 _ Military surface mail to Africa, Greenland, the Middle
East and Southeast Asia.
   Nov. 2 _ Military space available mail to the Middle East and
Southeast Asia.
   Nov. 4 _ Civilian surface mail to the Caribbean, Europe and
Central and South America.
   Nov. 7 _ Military space available mail to Australia and military
surface mail to the Caribbean, Central and South America.
   Nov. 9 _ Military PAL mail to Africa, the Middle East and
Southeast Asia.
   Nov. 14 _ Military space available mail to Europe, the Far East,
Greenland and Central and South America.
   Nov. 21 _ Civilian air letters and cards to Southeast Asia and
civilian air parcels and to Southeast Asia, Middle East, Australia
and Africa. Military space available mail to the Caribbean.
   Nov. 23 _ Military PAL mail to Australia, Europe, Far East,
Greenland, Central and South America. Military space available mail
to Alaska. Military surface mail to Alaska and Hawaii.
   Nov. 24 _ Civilian air letters and cards to Australia and the
Middle East. Military PAL mail to the Caribbean.
   Dec. 1 _ Military PAL mail to Alaska.
   Dec. 2 _ Civilian air letters and cards to Africa, Europe, Far
East and Greenland. Civilian air parcels to Europe, Far East and
Greenland.
   Dec. 5 _ Civilian air letters, cards and parcels to Central and
South America.
   Dec. 7 _ Civilian air letters, cards and parcels to Alaska and
Hawaii.
   Dec. 9 _ Civilian air letters, cards and parcels to the
Caribbean.
