<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--MilitaryMoves     09-07 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Military Moves,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>RisCassi Chosen for No. 2 Army Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has nominated Lt. Gen. Robert
W. RisCassi for promotion to four-star general and appointment as
vice chief of staff for the Army, the Pentagon said Wednesday.
   Assuming Senate confirmation, RisCassi, 52, would succeed the
retiring Gen. Arthur E. Brown Jr. as the Army's second-ranking
officer, the Pentagon said.
   RisCassi, a native of Hartford, Conn., now is director of the
joint staff for the Joint Chiefs of Staff. He would be replaced in
that post by Air Force Lt. Gen. Hansford T. Johnson, 52, the
Pentagon said.
   Johnson, a native of Aiken, S.C., now is deputy
commander-in-chief of the U.S. Central Command, the organization
responsible for all American forces in the Middle East.
