<1ST_LINE>r w AM-MailEmbargo     09-07 0124</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Mail Embargo,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.S. Halts Shipping Mail to Britain</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Britain-Mail Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Postal Service announced Wednesday it
is immediately embargoing mail to Britain because of a strike by
postal workers in that country.
   British postal deliveries are nearly at a halt and 100 million
pieces of undelivered mail have piled up in a week-old nationwide
strike that idled more than half of the country's 180,000 postal
workers.
   The embargo ``was requested by the British postal administration
because of it's inability to handle any volume of mail,'' a Postal
Service statement said.
   Mail to Britain will be returned to senders. People who get such
mail back can apply to their local post office for a refund of the
postage.
</TEXT>
