   Humorist Jerry Clower says telling funny
stories may not be all he does Friday night on the stage of the
Grand Ole Opry.
   He plans to whip up some spirit for Mississippi State, his alma
mater. The school's football team plays against Vanderbilt
University on Saturday in Nashville.
   Clower, who played defensive tackle for Mississippi State in
1949 and 1950, won't be able to attend the game because he's
scheduled to make an appearance in Ada, Okla. But he says his
appearance on the Grand Ole Opry on Friday night may turn into a
minipep rally.
   ``I know there's gonna be a bunch of Mississippi State fans on
hand, so I may do me a cheer right there on stage,'' he said.
</TEXT>
