<HEAD>Kidnapped Industrialist Frees Himself</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLATI, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alberto Minervini, bearded, in tattered
clothes and with a chain around his neck, arrived at a police
station Wednesday and said he had freed himself from kidnappers who
seized him a month ago.
   The 58-year-old industrialist from Naples and his 15-year-old
grandson were abducted Aug. 5 while vacationing in southern
Calabria. The teen-ager was released the next day, presumably to
pass on a ransom demand.
   Several thousand police joined the hunt, but to no avail.
   Police said Minervini had been chained to a pole and was in weak
physical condition. They said he gave no details of his escape.
