<1ST_LINE>r a AM-OldHomicide     09-07 0330</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Old Homicide,0339</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seek to Reopen 10-Year-Old Case After Victim Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former Walt Disney World costume designer
died 10 years after she was beaten so badly she was unable to walk,
talk or feed herself, and police are seeking to reopen the case.
   Blanche Wendelin, 69, died over the weekend in her daughters'
home in Fort Lauderdale, where she had lived since an eight-month
hospitalization that followed the September 1978 attack. After an
autopsy Monday, the Broward County medical examiner's office ruled
the death a homicide.
   An acquaintance was investigated in connection with the beating,
but was never charged. The statute of limitations ran out a year
after the beating when police were unable to gather enough evidence
to file charges, and all information about the case was removed
from the suspect's file.
   But under a new state law, homicide charges can be filed
whatever the length of time between the injuries and the death.
   Orlando detectives are bound by court order not to talk about
details of the case, said spokesman Sgt. Mike Holloway. But he said
are seeking an opinion from the Orange County state attorney's
office on whether the case can be reopened and charges pursued
against the suspect.
   ``If they can make something of it, I say go after his blood,''
said Marilyn Nevandomski, one of the victim's daughters. ``Nobody
should be able to do that to another human being and get away with
it, no matter how much time has passed.''
   Ms. Wendelin helped design and make costumes for the puppets in
the ``It's a Small World'' attraction at Disney World. Four years
ago, she went back in her wheelchair for a VIP tour, her daughter
said.
   But her life had become difficult in recent years as she was
forced to depend on others.
   ``We really lost her 10 years ago,'' said Ms. Nevandomski. ``The
way she was before and the way she was after, there's no
comparing.''
</TEXT>
