<HEAD>Italy Raises Speed Limit To 81 MPH</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Cabinet on Wednesday approved an increase in the
speed limit on superhighways to 81 mph but voted to retain a new 68
mph limit on holidays.
   The government lowered speed limits in July in an effort to
reduce accidents in holiday traffic.
   Before the summer, the limit for superhighways was 87 mph and
the limit for smaller highways was 68 mph. The superhighway limit
was changed in July to 68 mph and the lower figure to 56 mph. The
Cabinet voted Wednesday to maintain the standard on smaller
highways.
   The lower limits raised protests from West Germany, whose
tourists flock to Italy in the summer.
   The Cabinet also approved a law making use of seat belts
mandatory beginning next year.
