   CHICAGO _ Two proteges of Beatrice Co. Chairman Donald P. Kelly,
a master dealmaker, say they have purchased a former Beatrice
subsidiary and plan to use it as a vehicle for other acquisitions.
   James M. Snodgrass and Steven S. Lindblad did not reveal Tuesday
what their investor group paid to buy Stiffel Co., a Chicago-based
