<HEAD>Boeing Gets Jet Orders From China</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf pvs, The twin-engine ..., with one graf to
restore dropped time element. Picks up 3rd graf pvs, The jets ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Boeing Co. says the Chinese government has
ordered three Boeing 757-200 jetliners in a deal valued at around
$125 million.
   The twin-engine, medium-range jets are scheduled to be delivered
to the Civil Aviation Administration of China's Guangzhou Regional
Administration beginning December 1989, Boeing said Tuesday.
   The jets will be equipped with Rolls-Royce RB211-535E4 engines
and configured to carry 200 passengers.
   CAAC Guangzhou will use the planes on its high-density routes to
Beijing, Shanghai and Guilin.
   Total orders for 757s have reached 368 from 23 operators
worldwide, Boeing said.
</TEXT>
