<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Britain-Stocks     09-07 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Broadly Lower At Midday</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Will be led after the closing</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were broadly lower at midday
Wednesday as sentiment was depressed by a continued lack of
institutional interest.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 12.7
points, or 0.7 percent, at 1,755.3 at about 12:30 p.m. local time.
   Dealers said prices were marked lower in what was called a
technical reaction to the solid gains of recent days, which also
came amid low trading volume.
   ``The last couple of days have been a false market,'' said one
dealer.
   In addition, weakness in the U.S. dollar sparked worries that
Wall Street might move lower later Wednesday. The New York market's
performance Tuesday gave little direction to London shares.
   Sharply lower crude oil prices triggered falls in oil shares,
with some dealers suggesting this pulled the overall market down.
   Volume was thin, with just 183.2 million shares changing hands
by midday.
</TEXT>
