more than $5 for each $1,000 in face value, putting their yields at
around the 9 percent level.
   And stock prices continued the rally they began late last week,
when monthly statistics on the employment situation showed slower
job growth.
   Stock-market bulls hope more economic data in the weeks ahead
will support the belief that growth has slowed of late, reducing
upward pressure on inflation and interest rates.
   Inflationary expectations also have been cooled this week by
falling oil prices.
   Gainers among the blue chips today included McDonald's, up } at
