<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Britain-IrishDistillers     09-07 0301</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Irish Distillers,0313</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Irish Court Upholds Order Barring Share Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Irish High Court on Wednesday confirmed an
injunction obtained by Pernod Ricard SA preventing FII Fyffes PLC
from disposing of its 20.04-percent holding in takeover target
Irish Distillers Group PLC.
   The High Court, sitting in Dublin, said it would reach a final
decision on the matter Oct. 6.
   Irish Distillers, Ireland's largest distiller, is the target of
competing takeover offers from friendly suitor Pernod Ricard, a
French liquor concern, and hostile bidder Grand Metropolitan PLC, a
British liquor company.
   Grand Metropolitan has made a sweetened offer of 332 million
Irish punts, the equivalent of $479 million, or 525 Irish pence a
share for Irish Distillers.
   Pernod's offer, which has been approved by the Irish Distillers
board of directors, is for 285 million Irish punts, or 450 Irish
pence a share.
   The stake that FII Fyffes, an Irish fruit importer, holds in
Irish Distillers is seen as crucial to the outcome of the takeover
battle.
   Pernod claims a pledge by FII Fyffes last week to sell Pernod
its Irish Distillers shares should stand although Grand
Metropolitan subsequently came back with its higher offer.
   Irish Distillers said in a statement its shareholders should
know that if the high court upholds Pernod's injunction, the French
company will have above 50 percent of Irish Distillers' stock,
including the FII Fyffes stake.
   ``In the meantime, the board is not yet in a position to advise
shareholders as to what action they should take in connection with
their shares,'' Irish Distillers said.
   Irish Distillers stock shot up 49 pence to 415 pence a share on
London's Stock Exchange Wednesday afternoon after trading resumed
following a two-day suspension at Irish Distillers' request.
   Irish Distillers products include Irish whiskey brands
Jameson's, Powers, and Paddy.
</TEXT>
