<1ST_LINE>u f AM-AutoSales     09-07 0203</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Sales,0211</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toyota Reports August Sales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toyota Motor Sales USA Inc. said Wednesday it
sold 59.3 percent more U.S.-made cars in late August of this year
than during the same period last year.
   But for the month, the automaker reported a 10.2 percent decline
in the U.S. and foreign-made trucks and cars sold in the United
States.
   During the Aug. 21-31 period, Toyota said it sold 2,778 cars
made in the United States, compared with 1,744 during the same
period last year. There were nine selling days in both periods.
   When foreign-made cars and trucks sold in August are added in,
Toyota sold 86,743 vehicles last month, down from 92,066 vehicles
during August 1987.
   There were 27 selling days last month and 26 during the same
month last year. Percentages are drawn from comparisons of daily
sales rates.
   Most domestic and foreign car and truck makers Tuesday reported
sales of 1,281,378 vehicles during August of this year, compared
with 1,346,605 vehicles in August last year, an 8.4 percent decline.
   For the year, vehicle makers reported a 4.4 percent increase
from 9,949,273 vehicles during the first eight months of last year
to 10,440,498 during the same period this year.
</TEXT>
